Post Where
===========
Post Where is a prototype google app engine application for mapping blog posts.
It serves to plot location for which a blogpost was written. 
It currently supports only one location per post but future iterations can include 
mapping several locations (like tags) to a post.

The idea behind this project is that heatmaps can be created from this data to 
provide a visual representation of issues that pertain to a location being posted 
by citizen journalism. Dynamic map based data visualization of citizen journalism.

Please do well to check the attached LICENSE file. Thanl you.

Current features:
================
-submission of blog posts with its location
-listing of all submitted posts when not logged
-listing of only submitted posts of logged in user
-posting limited to logged in users
-info window displays when list item is clicked
-info window displays when marker is clicked




